### Sambandh API examples — signup flow
### Use the REST Client extension in VS Code to run these directly

@host = http://localhost:3010
@phone = +919876543210

### 1. Request OTP (frontend handles via Firebase SDK actually)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/request-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}"
}

###

### 2. Verify OTP — exchange Firebase ID token for our JWT
POST {{host}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}",
  "firebaseIdToken": "PASTE_FIREBASE_ID_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Response will include:
### { "token": "...", "user": { "id": "...", "phone": "...", "hasProfile": false, ... } }
### Save the token for subsequent requests.

###

@token = PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_PREVIOUS_RESPONSE

### 3. Complete signup — fill basic profile
POST {{host}}/api/auth/complete-signup
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Arjun",
  "gender": "male",
  "dob": "1997-08-15",
  "city": "Dibrugarh",
  "state": "Assam",
  "languages": ["assamese", "hindi", "english"]
}

###

### 4. Get current user
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
